  "runtimeMin": 90,
  "format": "Two days before the 96th Academy Awards, Sean Fennessey and Amanda Dobbins run all 23 categories, will-win and should-win, with Oppenheimer set to run the table. They split on only three calls: the animated and documentary shorts, and Best Sound, where Dobbins takes The Zone of Interest over Oppenheimer. The should-win picks wander further, both making a case for Killers of the Flower Moon. Recorded before the ceremony, so Lily Gladstone is the Best Actress call and Maestro the makeup pick. They close by grading the wild predictions they made back in October.",
